        // static content files
        '/home/guest/contact.md': { type: 'file', content: "Email: <a href='mailto:shajanjp@gmail.com' class='output-info' style='text-decoration:underline'>shajanjp at gmail dot com</a>\nGitHub:  <a href='https://github.com/shajanjp' target='_blank' class='output-highlight' style='text-decoration:underline'>github.com/shajanjp</a>\nLinkedIn: <a href='https://linkedin.com/in/shajanjp' target='_blank' class='output-highlight' style='text-decoration:underline'>linkedin.com/in/shajanjp</a>\n" },
        '/home/guest/about.md':   { type: 'file', content: "Hello,\n\nI'm Shajan Jacob - a software engineer and technical lead based in\nKochi, India, with over 8 years of experience designing and building\nproduction-grade web applications.\n\nI specialize in backend engineering with Node.js, TypeScript, and NestJS,\narchitecting scalable microservices and real-time systems on Google Cloud\nPlatform and AWS. My work spans high-throughput APIs, event-driven\narchitectures, and full-stack development - from ideation through deployment\nand beyond.\n\nCurrently, I serve as Technical Lead at Sorice Solutions (sorice.solutions),\nwhere I lead architecture decisions, mentor engineers, optimize system\nperformance, and drive end-to-end project delivery. Previously, I was a\nSoftware Engineer at Cubet Techno Labs (cubettech.com), where I built APIs,\nmicroservices, and serverless solutions, and published the ffmpeg-sdk npm\npackage.\n\nBeyond the keyboard, I'm deeply curious about hardware. The green traces\non circuit boards fascinated me as a child, and that curiosity grew into a\npassion for IoT and building things with Raspberry Pi, ESP32, and addressable\nLEDs. I've built everything from internet-connected Christmas stars to smart\nAC controllers - blending software with the physical world.\n\nWhen I'm not coding or tinkering, you'll find me spending time with family,\nreading a good book, shooting photographs, or getting lost on the internet\nlearning something new.\n\nI believe great engineering is about people as much as code - whether it's\nmentoring junior developers, collaborating with cross-functional teams, or\nbuilding tools that make someone's day a little easier.\n\nI also maintain a shelf of books and a uses page with the tools and gadgets\nI rely on.\n\nWant to work together or just say hello? Get in touch.\n" },
        '/home/guest/cv.md':      { type: 'file', content: "SHAJAN JACOB\nSoftware Engineer | Kochi, Kerala, India\nshajanjp at gmail dot com | shajanjacob.com\n\nв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓ\nPROFESSIONAL SUMMARY\nв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓ\nSoftware Engineer with 8+ years of experience in web applications\ndevelopment, specializing in Node.js, TypeScript, and scalable microservices.\nProven track record in system optimization, deployments, and team leadership.\n\nв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓ\nTECHNICAL SKILLS\nв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓ\nNode.js, JavaScript, TypeScript, NestJS, Express.js, Deno, REST API,\nMicroservices, Event-driven Architecture, Real-time Applications,\nGoogle Cloud Platform, AWS (Lambda, EC2, API Gateway, S3),\nFirebase Functions, Docker, Kubernetes, Nginx, MongoDB, PostgreSQL,\nMySQL, Redis, Elasticsearch, gRPC, Kafka, FHIR, JWT, Auth0, Stripe\n\nв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓ\nPROFESSIONAL EXPERIENCE\nв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓ\n\nSorice Solutions, Kochi вЂ” Technical Lead (Feb 2020 - Present)\n  - Architected core system architectures and key application features,\n    enhancing scalability, reliability, and maintainability.\n  - Migrated legacy apps to modern frameworks, cutting modification time\n    by 20%.\n  - Optimized high-throughput APIs handling 300K+ daily requests, improving\n    response times by 25%.\n  - Remediated security vulnerabilities, reducing incidents and improving\n    compliance.\n  - Optimized releases with robust deployment plans, cutting release-related\n    incidents.\n  - Contributed to AI integration efforts, researching and implementing\n    relevant tools.\n  - Developed internal tools and automation scripts to streamline tasks.\n  - Conducted merge request reviews and mentored junior developers.\n  - Led hiring for engineering roles, interviewing 300+ candidates.\n  - Contributed to end-to-end project execution: planning, estimation,\n    development, delivery, and cross-team collaboration.\n\nCubet, Kochi вЂ” Software Engineer (Oct 2017 - Feb 2020)\n  - Architected and developed custom APIs, microservices, and serverless\n    solutions (AWS Lambda, Firebase FaaS).\n  - Published the ffmpeg-sdk NPM package powering an online dubbing studio.\n  - Built a scalable Twitter chat engine supporting multiple chatbots per\n    Node.js instance, with real-time text/audio chat via sockets.\n  - Delivered end-to-end software solutions from prototyping to deployment.\n\nAlt S Solutions, Kochi вЂ” Junior Software Engineer (May 2017 - Oct 2017)\n  - Developed responsive websites tailored to diverse client requirements.\n  - Designed and implemented dashboards and APIs for a CRM application.\n\nв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓ\nEDUCATION\nв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓ\nBachelor of Engineering in CS\nT John Institute of Technology, Bangalore (2017)\n\nв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓ\nACHIEVEMENTS\nв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓ\n  - Ranked in the top 2% globally in LinkedIn's JavaScript skill assessment.\n  - Awarded \"Project of the Year\" for final-year campus project.\n\nв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓ\nHOBBY / SIDE PROJECTS\nв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓ\nMerry Pixels вЂ” Internet-connected Christmas star with 300 addressable LEDs.\n  TypeScript | Deno | Socket | HTML | Tailwind\n  merry-pixels.deno.dev\n\nCommunity Portal вЂ” Local business and services directory for residents.\n  TypeScript | Deno | Fresh | Notion API | Tailwind\n  piravom.in\n\nHN вЂ” Minimalistic Hacker News reader and PWA.\n  PWA | JavaScript | jQuery | Semantic-UI | Firebase\n  guyswhocode.com/HN/\n\nLets All Chef вЂ” Companion for home cooks: recipes, cookbooks, meal planning.\n  NodeJS | ExpressJS | MongoDB | Semantic-UI\n  letsallchef.github.io\n\nBlackPipe вЂ” Expose terminal outputs without sacrificing security.\n  NodeJS | Sockets | Semantic-UI | ExpressJS\n  shajanjacob.com/blackpipe/\n\nMeemi вЂ” Online ornamental fish store, forum, store locator and wiki.\n  NodeJS | ExpressJS | MongoDB | Elastic Search | SemanticUI\n\nв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓ\nPROFILES\nв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓ\n  linkedin.com/in/shajanjp\n  github.com/shajanjp\n  npmjs.com/~shajanjp\n\nв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓ\nHOBBIES\nв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓ\n  Terrariums, Photography, Crafting\n" },
        '/home/guest/welcome.md': { type: 'file', content: "Welcome to shajanjacob.com!\n\nThis terminal lets you explore the site contents.\n\n  cd projects  вЂ” browse {{ collections.projects.length }} projects\n  cd blog      вЂ” read {{ collections.blog.length }} blog posts\n  cd photos    вЂ” view {{ collections.photos.length }} photos\n  cd shortcuts вЂ” check out {{ collections.shortcuts.length }} shortcuts\n\nUse ls, cd, and cat to navigate. Type help for all commands.\n" },

        // system dirs
        '/etc': { type: 'dir', children: ['hostname', 'motd'] },
